HEADWORD: Manx cat
<hw>Manx cat</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <def>A breed
of domestic cats having a rudimentary tail, containing only about three
vertebrae. It is believed to have originated on the Isle of
Man.</def>⟦br⟧
